# Testing Standards

Docs: [testing.md](../../apps/web/docs/testing.md)

## Query order (most to least preferred)

1. `getByRole` — reflects assistive technology
2. `getByLabelText` — form inputs
3. `getByText` — visible text
4. `getByTestId` — last resort only

Never query by class name or CSS selector.

## Accessibility — target: WCAG 2.2 AA

Every `ui/` or interactive component test must include an axe assertion:

```tsx
import { axe } from 'vitest-axe'
it('has no accessibility violations', async () => {
  const { container } = render(<MyComponent />)
  expect(await axe(container)).toHaveNoViolations()
})
```

## Mock conventions

```ts
// next/image
vi.mock('next/image', () => ({
  default: ({ src, alt, width, height }: React.ImgHTMLAttributes<HTMLImageElement>) => (
    // eslint-disable-next-line @next/next/no-img-element
    <img src={src} alt={alt} width={width} height={height} />
  ),
}))

// @/sanity/image (urlFor)
vi.mock('@/sanity/image', () => ({
  urlFor: () => ({ width: () => ({ height: () => ({ url: () => 'https://cdn.example.com/img.jpg' }) }) }),
}))

// next-sanity/hooks
vi.mock('next-sanity/hooks', () => ({ useIsPresentationTool: () => false }))
```

## Zustand

Reset store state in `afterEach` to prevent test bleed:

```ts
afterEach(() => { useMyStore.setState(initialState) })
```
